### For local testing, use:
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000
### For production (Render), use:
### @baseUrl = https://your-render-app.onrender.com

@email = jane@example.com
@password = Password123!
@userId = 2
@taskId = 1
@streakId = 1
@badgeId = 1
@quoteId = 1
@globalTaskId = 2
@personalTaskId = 1

### User IDs:
### 1 = newtasker@example.com
### 2 = odhi@gmail.com
### 3 = timothykhalayi96@gmail.com
### 4 = nandwatimothykhalayi@gmail.com

### Option A: paste tokens manually after login
@accessToken =
@refreshToken =

### Option B: if your REST Client supports named-response variables
@accessToken = {{login.response.body.$.accessToken}}
@refreshToken = {{login.response.body.$.refreshToken}}
@userId = {{login.response.body.$.user.id}}

### ==================== HEALTH + DOCS ====================

### Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/

### Swagger docs (should return HTML)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/docs

### OpenAPI JSON (should return JSON)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/docs-json


### ==================== AUTH ====================

### Register new tasker user
# @name register
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

